			<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/fb37f81f28c9408c885f0bbe33a00a71?s=74&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D74&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-74 photo' height='74' width='74' />			<cite class="fn">Luiz</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://calnewport.com/blog/2014/04/20/richard-feynman-didnt-win-a-nobel-by-responding-promptly-to-e-mails/#comment-174906">
			April 22, 2014 at 5:59 am</a>		</div>

		<p>Cal,</p>
<p>Here is more evidence against the passion myth. </p>
<p>Magnus Carson, 23, is the current world chess champion and chess prodigy. His father taught him to play chess at the age of 5, although he initially showed little interest in the game.</p>
<p>If he had chess written into his genes he would have been passionate about chess from the start.</p>

		<div class="reply">
			<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/blog/2014/04/20/richard-feynman-didnt-win-a-nobel-by-responding-promptly-to-e-mails/?replytocom=174906#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-174906", "174906", "respond", "3527")'>Reply</a>		</div>
				</div>
