		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://calnewport.com/blog/2014/04/20/richard-feynman-didnt-win-a-nobel-by-responding-promptly-to-e-mails/#comment-175050">
			April 22, 2014 at 6:36 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Sometimes passions develop with practice. If the passion never develops, then you will burn out before becoming world class. Passion is still critical to succeed.</p>

